---
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import Hero from '~/components/widgets/Hero.astro';
import Content from '~/components/widgets/Content.astro';
import CallToAction from '~/components/widgets/CallToAction.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Pursuing Revenue - CXO Atlas',
  description: 'Optimizing profitability and maximizing revenue. Get practical guidance for entrepreneurs focused on financial performance.',
  keywords: 'revenue optimization, profitability, financial performance, business growth, revenue maximization',
  canonical: 'https://cxo-atlas.com/article/pursuing-revenue'
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <Hero
    title="Pursuing Revenue"
    subtitle="Optimizing profitability and maximizing revenue. Get practical guidance for entrepreneurs focused on financial performance."
    actions={[
      { text: 'Browse All Articles', href: '/article', variant: 'primary' },
      { text: 'Back to Journey Map', href: '/#journey' },
    ]}
    image={{ src: '~/assets/images/hero-image.png', alt: 'Pursuing Revenue' }}
  />

  <Content
    id="revenue-content"
    class="py-16 md:py-24"
    background="light"
  >
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
        <h2>Stage 9: Pursuing Revenue</h2>
        
        <p>You've built a solid business with good operations. Now it's time to focus on maximizing profitability and revenue. This is about fine-tuning your business model for optimal financial performance.</p>

        <h3>What This Stage Looks Like</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>You have stable operations and processes</li>
          <li>You're focused on revenue optimization</li>
          <li>You're analyzing and improving unit economics</li>
          <li>You're exploring new revenue streams</li>
          <li>You're maximizing customer lifetime value</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Key Challenges</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Revenue Optimization:</strong> Maximizing revenue from existing customers</li>
          <li><strong>Pricing Strategy:</strong> Finding the optimal price points</li>
          <li><strong>Cost Management:</strong> Reducing costs without sacrificing quality</li>
          <li><strong>New Revenue Streams:</strong> Identifying and developing additional income sources</li>
          <li><strong>Financial Planning:</strong> Long-term financial strategy and planning</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>What You Need to Know</h3>
        <p>This stage is about financial optimization. You need to understand your unit economics deeply and find ways to improve them. It's about working on the business, not just in it.</p>

        <h3>Critical Focus Areas</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Unit economics and profitability analysis</li>
          <li>Pricing strategy and optimization</li>
          <li>Customer lifetime value maximization</li>
          <li>Cost structure optimization</li>
          <li>Revenue diversification and growth</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Revenue Optimization Strategies</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Upselling & Cross-selling:</strong> Increasing revenue per customer</li>
          <li><strong>Pricing Optimization:</strong> Testing and improving price points</li>
          <li><strong>Customer Retention:</strong> Reducing churn and increasing lifetime value</li>
          <li><strong>Operational Efficiency:</strong> Reducing costs and improving margins</li>
          <li><strong>New Product Development:</strong> Creating additional revenue streams</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Financial Metrics to Track</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Gross margin and net margin</li>
          <li>Customer acquisition cost (CAC)</li>
          <li>Customer lifetime value (CLV)</li>
          <li>Monthly recurring revenue (MRR)</li>
          <li>Revenue growth rate and predictability</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Long-term Considerations</h3>
        <p>At this stage, you're also thinking about long-term strategic options like acquisitions, partnerships, or exit strategies. You've built a valuable business that others might want to acquire.</p>

        <div class="bg-teal-50 dark:bg-teal-900/20 p-6 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-teal-500">
          <h4>ðŸ’Ž Pro Tip</h4>
          <p>Focus on sustainable growth over short-term gains. Build a business that can generate consistent, predictable revenue over the long term. That's what creates real value.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Content>

  <CallToAction
    id="revenue-cta"
    class="py-16 md:py-24"
    background="dark"
    title="Ready to Start Your Journey?"
    subtitle="Get practical guidance for every stage of your entrepreneurial journey."
    actions={[
      { text: 'Back to Journey Map', href: '/#journey', variant: 'primary' },
      { text: 'Browse All Articles', href: '/article' },
    ]}
  />
</Layout>
